President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key positions in his administration. Christopher Caldwell of Arkansas is nominated to be the Federal Co-Chairman of the Delta Regional Authority. Walter Copan of Colorado is nominated to be the Under Secretary of Commerce for Standards and Technology. Brian D. Montgomery of Texas is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Housing and Urban Development, Federal Housing Commissioner. George Bryan Slater of Virginia is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Labor, Administration and Management. Glen R. Smith of Iowa is nominated to be a Member of the Farm Credit Administration Board. James E. Trainor III of Texas is nominated to be a Commissioner of the Federal Election Commission.